olive oil
1 carrot
2 clove garlic
1 packet pork schnitzels
1 packet jasmine rice
1 packet broccoli florets
2 tbs plain flour
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 sachet sesame seeds
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
20 g butter
1 tsp soy sauce

• Boil the kettle.
• Cut carrot into thin sticks. Finely chop garlic.
• In a small microwave-safe bowl, place the butter and garlic and microwave in 10 second bursts or until melted. Set aside.

• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Add jasmine rice and a pinch of salt.
• Place a colander or steamer basket on top of saucepan and add carrot and broccoli florets. Cook, covered with a lid, over high heat until tender, 12-14 minutes.
• Transfer veggies to a medium bowl and season to taste. Cover to keep warm. Drain rice, return to saucepan and stir through garlic butter.

• Meanwhile, in a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour, salt and sweet soy seasoning. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, combine panko breadcrumbs, sesame seeds and olive oil (2tbs for 2 people / 1/4 cup for 4 people).
• Dip pork into flour mixture to coat, followed by the egg, and finally in breadcrumbs. Set aside on a plate.
• Set your air fryer to 200°C. Place crumbed pork into air fryer basket and cook, turning halfway, until golden and cooked through, 6-8 minutes.

TIP: No air fryer? Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base. Cook pork schnitzel in batches until golden and cooked through, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

• To a second small microwave-safe bowl add plum sauce, the soy sauce and a splash of water. Microwave in 10 second bursts, until heated through.
• Divide garlic rice, pork schnitzel and steamed veggies between bowls. Drizzle over sticky sweet chilli sauce. Enjoy!